	<p>I kinda gotta take Lit's back on this one . On my server at least the majority of guilds dont recruite shaman . However they would GLADLY take Clerics , Rogues , Wizards , beastlords , bards and basicly any outher class .<br />
I think its safe too say that as far as established guild desireability in the current state of everquest that Shamans are pretty low on the totem pole .. maybe not DEAD LAST but were prety low down there .<br />
I do think that is becase once you have 3-5 established full time shamans you really dont benifit hugely from adding more .<br />
Everquest has become a Fast paced game where FAST HEALING .. FAST DAMAGE and TANKABILITY are the 3 defining charicteristics one of the major factors in how "desireable" a class is too a guilld is stackability ... IF your class dosent stack well you will not be as needed as a Class that does .<br />
It used too be that sure we didnt stack BUT if a guild didnt have a shaman or two MAN were we missed .. these days though the BUT has been removed any high end guild will ALLWAYS have at least one or two shamans and heck if they dont .. they'll bot one .</p>
	
	
	
	
	
