<tr>
	<td class="alt1" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Blazz</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Mystic<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Sep 2003<br />
	Location: Upstate, NY
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>A. Its certainly not "any other class". Monks, SKs, Paladins, and Warriors with less than 10K hps and under 300 aa arent exactly getting invited anywhere either. <br />
<br />
B. Shaman is one of those classes thats burning out quickly in the new enviroment. This week they may not need shaman. Next week they might. Seriously. <br />
<br />
C. We are making noise. We are making progress. I remember when Rangers were the laughing stock of the game. I remember when Rogues were the worst class around. I remember when Warriors were only desirable on raids, and couldnt get XP groups. The game goes through phases. Honestly, when SOE dev's create content, I doubt they go "but how will this affect shamans?" They have a LONG history of putting out crap, then adjusting and tweaking. Necros are useful. Bards arent a joke anymore. Yeah, it sucks that this is "our" phase. There shouldnt be phases at all. But they happen. We have been slipping in desirability since the end of Kunark. Fortunately, our insane powerfulness carried us through a lot of it. Now, its gone. BLs have replaced us in a lot of ways. Druids got much better improvements in healing. Chanters are a combination of buff, debuff, and insane DPS in some encoutners that no one can compete with them. Thats the way the river flows. But I think we have made our point. I think they are listening. <br />
<br />
I am not a nay-sayer who thinks SOE doesnt listen to its users. Warriors made a stink, and got some nice changes, changes that made them MUCH better 1-group options for tanking than they were. Other classes have sucked, and been adjusted. Content tends to obsolete things in the game the dev's never seem to consider. I am not defending this, I am merely pointing out that they HAVE adjusted it in the past, and there is no reason to think we wont be adjusted as well.</p>
	
	
	
