	<p>I think our desirability is decreased by the fact that (at least on my server) every  other paladin/SK has a shaman alt.   So even if you have a shortage of Main type shaman there is always one available to at least do malos/slow.  A bot shaman might not bring nearly as much to the table as a main but they can certainly cast malos and slow effectively enough.  Add the the fact that most guild will have several 65 bots and i some of those bots are nicely equiped with a decent number of AA's.<br />
<br />
In a strange way it isn't that we are undesirable which hurts us but that every hybrid wants a pocket shaman, we are too desirable.  How many other classes do you see rolling wizzy or rogue alts, there might be a couple but not many.<br />
<br />
And a shaman's main duties on a raid, unlike a pullers or cleric in CHR, are easily bottable.  That plus a lack of stackablility does hurt us.  But I would still rather be a shaman then sit in a CHR any day of the week <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="smile" smilieid="1" />.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
