<tr>
	<td class="alt1" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Valsuvious</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Mystic<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Aug 2002<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>I really think that if you want to go somewhere, come to my server then.  Every high end guild needs shaman, and until we just found another shaman, I had been running around for a while as the only raiding shaman.  Ideally, I'd like to have 3 - 4 on every night depending on the content.  2 shaman in the Ikk raids are good, but 3 for Ikk 4 and a solid 3 - 4 in uqua at least.  <br />
<br />
Personally I know the top three guilds on my server are recruiting shaman.<br />
<br />
I would not take a shaman bot and let them raid with me.  No way.  I do let one person come and park themselves near uqua if we are short and only i am present, but that is only for MGB purposes and they serve no other function.  <br />
<br />
Any class can be botted on a raid.  However, a best bot is only as good as the worst non-botted person.  If that's not the case, than maybe you should look at that person and ask why aren't they performing up to standards.  Sure you can sit there and hit the malos key when the mob is in camp and then slow it, but in that time, I would have already had the mob slowed and someone else buffed.  <br />
<br />
Let's face it though, how many classes can get away with having a huge number of people there and almost not be considered taking up valuable space. Well, you always need damage and why not take the best two classes for dps -- wizard and rogues.  You always need people to heal, so clerics stack well.  You always need people to tank stuff, so Warriors are great to have around too.  After that, there is a severe drop off in rest of classes needed.  Too many shaman around, not enough mobs to slow.  Too many chanters around, not enough mobs that need mezzing.  Too many rangers around, not enough mobs to kill them.  <br />
<br />
How do you really know if you are trying to maximize your damage output in a shaman role?  When you are one of the first ones to always get summoned when the tank goes down.  I tend to be #2 alot, after our best mage.  Just tonight I got summoned three times in Glorification when the mobs were at 0 - 5%, and most of them were just from one bane cast, and alot of crit nuking <img src="images/smilies/frown.gif" border="0" alt="" title="frown" smilieid="2" /></p>
	
	
	
