<tr>
	<td class="alt2" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Karaab Stormbringer</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Disciple<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Jan 2003<br />
	Location: Wisconsin, US
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>... and for once, I actually somewhat agree with Val here (mark your calendars!)<br />
<br />
Thursday night I was just "chillin" in PoK, when I got a tell from a PoP progressing, but <b>very</b> casual guild who, surprisingly, had tons of shamans in guild, but 0 online for Aerin`Dar. Originally, I was asked if I had the flag (already did), but since I wasn't doing anything else (and was insanely bored at the time), I offered my services and they were accepted.<br />
<br />
One thing led to another, Aerin`Dar died... Rydda got walled and decided to wig out and leave everybody as a nice smear on the floor... and the leader and I got to talking. Apparently, most of their shamans now (despite having quite a number OF them) can't make Thursday, Saturday, and Sunday nights, at all. How do I know this?<br />
<br />
Saturday night - Started with 4 shamans, ended with 2 of them.<br />
Sunday night - Started with 2, ended with ... 1.<br />
<br />
Granted, it <b>IS</b> a holiday in the US, people might be travelling and the like (craziness considering the price of gas right now, if you ask me) and the situation may be different in a week, but that's my observations, from a fairly heavily populated server no less.<br />
<br />
So... in <i>some</i> situations, shamans are still indispensible, sure... but unfortunately, the newer the content is, (and summarily, the faster it takes to ... take it out) the less that's getting to be the case. I can understand not wanting to have a half hour long fight (been there, done that, few times... even more boring than watching paint dry), but when it goes from "somewhat balanced around that" to "suddenly not"... that's time to step back and go "Ok... where do we go from here?"</p>
	
	
	
		<div>__________________<br />Elder Karaab Silverwind, Prophet of the Dar Khura<br />
Rodcet Nife<br />
