</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>The first time my friends and I tried Aerin'Dar, it was a Shaman that pulled him.  <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="smile" smilieid="1" /><br />
<br />
I've found that there were very few Shaman around and now it seems like every one of my friends has made a Shaman alternate.  They may be twinked and have some better gear than I do, but over four years of playing a Shaman gives me some insight into how to work with other classes and fill in some gapes.  <br />
<br />
The guilds that have 2 - 3 Shaman and don't think they need more are sadly mistaken.  In my 40s I was with a group in Dreadlands.  We were three Shaman, 1 Shadow Knight and 1 Warrior.  One Shaman debuffed, the second one did DD and the third one healed.  Buffs were rotated between the three of us.  It was one of the fastest exp groups I ever had there.</p>
	
	
	
