	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>That is not really true. A lot of encounters have significant off-tanking/CC requirements, and in those cases what happens on the main target is allmost trivial in comparison, its all about being in control of the adds. In some cases knights are preferred MTs. You generally need more than one warrior as well, at least 3, preferably more than that. Most successfull guilds maintain balanced line-ups to be able to deal effectively with whatever they come up against. The composition you are describing can only deal with one type of raid target.<br />
<br />
You also have to remember that raids are more than just killing the main target, there is allways a considerable amount of trash that needs to be pulled/split/killed/CCed. You need the capability to deal with that as well, just having a tank along with a bunch of clerics and wizards isnt going to get you too far.</p>
	
	
	
