	<!-- message -->
	<p>I have been class lead in my guild for almost a year and we was raiding mostly EP.<br />
At one time we got short of shamans and usually we had 1 or 2 online at raid time only (Note that it was possible to raid anyway).<br />
<br />
I am just gonna cover the MGBble stuff on this post.<br />
<br />
Sad but true I had to explain to the guild leader that 3 shamans (only) are needed to get the job done (1 rebuff/2debuff-slow). He ended up recruiting more anyway which made it even easier for us. <br />
<br />
One of the reasons (not the only one) why enchanters are more wanted is because they need to MGB more spells than we need. Few of them at the raid means that nobody can mgb haste at some times.<br />
Once we MGB focus we just do the rest group by group with no problems and the spells will last long enough for mgb to pop back up.<br />
Same with the druids...  sometimes they need 4 of them (with mgb up)just to rotate SoW during a fight.<br />
<br />
<b>IMO a very easy way for Sony to make shamans more desirable on raids is to give them something similar to paragon/SoW to mgb.<br />
Something nice for a shaman would be a heal overtime that every tick cure poison and disease (or even curse)</b>.<br />
<br />
This would be just one little change to help out the shamans.<br />
<br />
Stanislao - Drinal</p>
	
	
	
	
	
