<tr>
	<td class="alt2" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Predicus</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Initiate<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Oct 2003<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Originally Posted by <b>PennyAntics</b><br /><i>Litgruv, this is an issue of stacking, not desireability.<br />
<br />
Shaman stacking has been an issue for a very long time, one that has never been addressed even partially. All guilds, no matter where they are in progression, need about 3 or 4 active raiding shaman MAX. This is to complete all buffs, and help with slowing. If a raiding guild has 3 or 4 shaman, another one is worthless. No job can be done by 5 shaman that cannot be done by 4.<br />
<br />
That being said, the desireability of EQ classes breaks down as follows. This is a huge flaw in everquest.<br />
<br />
1) Wizard<br />
2) Cleric<br />
3) Wizard<br />
4) Bard<br />
5) Mage<br />
6) Wizard<br />
7) Wizard<br />
8) Enchanter<br />
9) Wizard<br />
10) Warrior<br />
11) Shaman<br />
12) Pally/SK<br />
13) Wizard<br />
<br />
In short, the "trio" of grouping is trivial in raiding content. Raids require four classes. One very good warrior, enough clerics to spam supernal light long enough to keep anyone alive through a fight, a bard for each group (Bards are better slowers in the raid scenario than shaman or enchanters) to render everyone immune to AOEs and increase DPS of the raid by ~33%, and a whole sh!tload of wizards.<br />
<br />
The wizard is, right now, the king of burst DPS. This is why the unbeatable raid strategy is keep the main tank alive, and have every single one of your 29015 wizards crit Strike of Solusek at the same time. All other tasks are trivial in comparison. Kill fast, now, take precautions later.<br />
<br />
I challenge you to find a guild that says "not needed" under wizard applications. This is because they have a reverse stacking algorithm; the MORE wizards you have, the BETTER they become, because aggro can be spread among them, while maintaining DPS.<br />
<br />
The wizard is the most broken class in the game, shortly followed by bard, then cleric. That is the raiding trio, the force that cannot be stopped. All they need is a warrior or knight pawn to hit taunt for them and no target is too tough to beat.</i><hr size="1" /></blockquote>     Another reason why you see guilds recruiting clerics/wizards/rogues constantly is due to the fact that these three classes burn out fast.  Each class is top in their department: cleric/healing; wizard/spell dps; rogue/melee dps.  The catch to this is that outside of their area of expertise is that there is little "constructive" utility, and hence a lot of players get bored with them.  Shamans have a lot of utility (some trivialized with new content), and that is why we see some many " 5 years and counting.." shamans on the servers.  If we don't feel like raiding/grouping we can always fall back to soloing- something not all classes can do efficiently.  <br />
     From what I have viewed on Brell, there is a large lack in shaman availability outside of raids.  I used to /role when I wanted to hide from grouping, but even that is not working as well anymore.  There are other shamans out there, but from what I have seen- many of them are very new.  A lot of these shamans have low aa counts, low hitpoints, and haven't progressed very far in PoP/GoD (not a bad thing, but sometimes not a viable option in specific scenarios.)  Some shamans don't canni, others are half-afk, and some just don't know what they are doing.  Many are alts, some are bots, and others are even ebay'ed; so it narrows down the availability of our class.  I find right now that slowers are desperately needed in Sol Ro, Elementals, and GoD just for the reason that there is literally no one on that is flagged/geared to mess with the content.  This is just the situation on Brell though, and could be very different on other servers.</p>
	
	
	
