	<p>It has nothing to do with alts. It has to do with the fact that the shamans don't offer ANY utility to the raid/groups other then slow and occasional, well placed/timed but crappy heal.<br />
<br />
Debuffs? Sorry, but mages and chanters can debuff as well, in addition to loads of utility spells and crowd control/useful summons/CoH and whatever. What does the shaman have to offer? A slow, a buff no one really misses because it's crappy, and, well, that's that. With slow mitigating mobs, or slow immune mobs, even that isn't such an issue, any bloody chanter or BST can slow in cases like this just as well. What do shamans have to offer in cases like this? DPS? Tanking? Healing? Good buffs? Nope. Nothing of that kind, literally every other class in these areas outperforms us easily. That's why there's really no need for more then 4 shamans max online on any guild raid either, because if there was more, they would simply have nothing to do. And that's only because we simply have not much else to offer.</p>
	
	
	
