	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Lit, I gotta toss this into the mix.<br />
<br />
You were proud of soloing/grouping (when you wanted to) for your career and then got tired of the game limitations. Now you have given the game another chance based on the premise that you are going to join a guild and make everything better. It hasn't happened, so the game once again sucks because "shaman" are not wanted/needed/whatever.<br />
<br />
I gotta pull the BS lever.<br />
<br />
Lack of stackability has ALWAYS been a shaman limitation. Of course it wasn't noticed because there were not that many folks playing shaman. Our biggest downfall was the period when everyone decided that shaman were flavor of the month. Thanks to those posting about soloing dragons in WW. Thanks again to them waving the 'power flag' in SOE's face resulting in no positive adjustments being made to a balanced class.<br />
<br />
Now there are simply too many shaman. The real downside is the majority of those are not shaman at all, but folks who made/got a shaman toon and haven't got clue-friggen-one how to play them. Actually, this comment can be attributed to many more than just shaman class.<br />
<br />
Long-to-short version of this is those shaman who excel, who have worked up with a guild and stuck with it, and who are 'real' shaman are very much in demand. I am not saying you are not one of those, Lit. I don't know you, or how you play your shaman. I am saying you left some steps out of your career path - and that was guilding. While your grouping reputation sounds solid, just like the difference between grouping and soloing is significant so is the difference between solo/grouping and being a raiding shaman. The slots available are few (always have been) and, regardless of who you know, for the higher end guilds your credentials better be outstanding as a raiding shaman if you want to be considered for one of the few slot.<br />
<br />
Personally, I think that sucks goats ... as does most of the limitations on raiding sizes/requirements that have nothing to do with the people playing but rather by game design/limitations.<br />
<br />
I have to add that I am 100% sure that at least 1 guild on each and every server is looking for at least 1 shaman to add to their ranks.<br />
<br />
Penny - your comment about 'read the chanter boards' takes the point chanters have discussed completely out of context. Chanters bring lots to the table and CC is still a very stong skill on that list. Note the word 'skill.'<br />
<br />
Putting on the class hat doesn't make you an expert at that class. You earn that on your own - whether shaman or enchanter or, even, wizard.</p>
	
	
	
