	<!-- message -->
	<p>I am kinda with Ltigruv on this one.<br />
<br />
I have been playing this shaman as my main toon for 4 years and some. I like to think that I am a fairly competent shaman too. I have been in small guilds, I have been in big guilds. I have been in 2 guilds that were, at the time, 3rd or 4th guild on the server.  Right now, I am interminably in an app guild for one of the big guilds. I have the min. requirements, I have the AA requirements, I have the resists requirements. I can't get in, basically, as far as I can tell, because there are enough shaman active in the guild. I don't even know if they are particularly competent shaman, because it doesn't, in my experience, require massive skill to be a raid shamam. Skill is required in anything from soloing up to about 2-grouping.<br />
<br />
So my gear sucks, and always will, and I do LDoNs and mooch around...</p>
	
	
	
